Defendant Nathaniel T Liedtke appears by videoconference from Milwaukee Secure Detention Facility, in custody.   Attorney Katie B. Bricco appears on behalf of Defendant.   Barbara Ann Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  State gives sentencing recommendation.  Attorney Bricco makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following: 

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9 MONTHS STRAIGHT TIME (CREDIT - 149 days credit, if revoked)

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS    *CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE*

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed/sign releases.
____Inform Agent of all prescriptions
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with: Cole B. or Biz Lab

RESTITUTION:  $50.00 to Cole B. (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)

COSTS:  $253.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation)
